'''守夜人國家'''（night-watchman state）是一種[[國家|國家]]形式，其以小政府為特點。在守夜人國家，政府的唯一角色就是透過[[軍隊|軍隊]]、[[警察|警察]]、[[法院|法院]]來確保每位公民皆在遵守[[互不侵犯原則|互不侵犯原則]]，以讓他們免受[[侵略_(社會科學)|侵略]]、[[偷竊|偷竊]]、[[違約|違約]]、[[詐騙|詐騙]]、財產法的干預。推廣它的人統稱為最小政府主義者（minarchists）<ref name="Gregory">Gregory, Anthony (2004-05-10). [http://www.strike-the-root.com/4/gregory/gregory6.html "The Minarchist's Dilemma"]. ''Strike the Root: A Journal of Liberty''. {{Wayback|url=http://www.strike-the-root.com/4/gregory/gregory6.html |date=20200112154257 }}. Retrieved 2020-02-01.</ref><ref name="Peikoff">Peikoff, Leonard (2011-03-07). [http://www.peikoff.com/2011/03/07/what-role-should-certain-specific-governments-play-in-objectivist-government "What role should certain specific governments play in Objectivist government?"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.peikoff.com/2011/03/07/what-role-should-certain-specific-governments-play-in-objectivist-government |date=20140912094317 }}. Peikoff.com. Retrieved 2020-01-02.</ref><ref name="Peikoff Part 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.peikoff.com/2011/10/03/interview-with-yaron-brook-on-economic-issues-in-todays-world-part-1/|title=Interview with Yaron Brook on economic issues in today's world (Part 1)|last=Peikoff|first=Leonard|publisher=Peikoff.com|date=2011-10-03|accessdate=2020-01-02|archive-date=2014-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140912102312/http://www.peikoff.com/2011/10/03/interview-with-yaron-brook-on-economic-issues-in-todays-world-part-1/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

此一類型的政体跟[[美國自由意志主義|美國自由意志主義]]、[[客觀主義|客觀主義]]、[[右派自由意志主義|右派自由意志主義]]等政治理念密切相關，不過[[無政府主義|無政府主義者]]以外的[[自由意志社會主義|自由意志社會主義者]]及左翼自由意志主義者同樣會支持最小政府主義<ref>Hain, Peter (2000). [https://www.chartist.org.uk/articles/britpol/july_hain.html "Rediscovering our libertarian roots"]. ''Chartist''. {{Wayback|url=https://www.chartist.org.uk/articles/britpol/july_hain.html |date=20130621010116 }}. Retrieved 2020-02-01.</ref><ref>Marshall, Peter (2009) [1991]. ''Demanding the Impossible: A History of Anarchism'' (POLS ed.). Oakland, California: PM Press. [https://books.googlecomt/books?id=QDWIOL_KtGYC&pg=PA641&dq=Left+libertarianism+can+therefore+range+from+the+decentralist+who+wishes+to+limit+and+devolve+State+power,+to+the+syndicalist+who+wants+to+abolish+it+altogether.+It+can+even+encompass+the+Fabians+and+the+social+democrats+who+wish+to+socialize+the+economy+but+who+still+see+a+limited+role+for+the+State&hl=it&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj9kfqN0bDnAhVDPFAKHcwfAngQ6AEIKzAA#v=onepage&q=Left%20libertarianism%20can%20therefore%20range%20from%20the%20decentralist%20who%20wishes%20to%20limit%20and%20devolve%20State%20power%2C%20to%20the%20syndicalist%20who%20wants%20to%20abolish%20it%20altogether.%20It%20can%20even%20encompass%20the%20Fabians%20and%20the%20social%20democrats%20who%20wish%20to%20socialize%20the%20economy%20but%20who%20still%20see%20a%20limited%20role%20for%20the%20State&f=false p. 641]{{Dead link|date=2020年6月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. "Left libertarianism can therefore range from the decentralist who wishes to limit and devolve State power, to the syndicalist who wants to abolish it altogether. It can even encompass the Fabians and the social democrats who wish to socialize the economy but who still see a limited role for the State." {{ISBN|978-1604860641}}.</ref>。一些無政府主義者及左翼自由意志主義者相信{{link-en|社會安全網|Social safety net}}對於工人階級而言只是短期的目標。長遠而言一旦國家及資本主義被推翻，那麼就不需要之。故此亦同樣支持建立最小限度的福利國家<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zmag.org/chomsky_repliesana.htm|title=Chomsky Replies to Multiple Questions About Anarchism|website=Z Magazine|publisher=ZCommunications|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929074956/https://www.zmag.org/chomsky_repliesana.htm|archivedate=2007-09-29|accessdate=2011-08-19|quote=Anarchists propose other measures to deal with these problems, without recourse to state authority. [...] Social democrats and anarchists always agreed, fairly generally, on so-called 'welfare state measures'.}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://anarchism.pageabode.com/afaq/secJ5.html|title=An Anarchist FAQ|editor-last=McKay|editor-first=Iain|volume=II|section=J.5 What alternative social organisations do anarchists create?|year=2012|location=Stirling|publisher=AK Press|isbn=978-1-849351-22-5|oclc=182529204|access-date=2020-05-23|archive-date=2020-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706172811/http://anarchism.pageabode.com/afaq/secJ5.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。另外一些左翼自由意志主義者認為在廢除[[社會福利|社會福利]]保障之前，應先废除{{link-en|公司福利|Corporate welfare}}<ref>Richman, Sheldon (2011-02-03). [http://www.theamericanconservative.com/blog/libertarian-left/ "Libertarian Left: Free-market anti-capitalism, the unknown ideal"]. ''The American Conservative''. {{Wayback|url=http://www.theamericanconservative.com/blog/libertarian-left/ |date=20190610075037 }}. Retrieved 2012-03-05. "[Left-libertarians] prefer that corporate privileges be repealed ''before'' the regulatory restrictions on how those privileges may be exercised."</ref>。

[[羅伯特·諾齊克|羅伯特·諾齊克]]在《[[無政府、國家與烏托邦|無政府、國家與烏托邦]]》（1974）中支持建立守夜人國家，使得此一概念變得普及起來<ref name="Nozick 1974">{{cite book|title=Anarchy, State, and Utopia|last=Nozick|first=Robert|publisher=Basic Books|year=1974|isbn=978-0-465-09720-3|url=https://archive.org/details/anarchystateutop00nozi}}</ref>。歴史學家查尔斯·汤森德形容，19世紀的[[英國|英國]]是守夜人國家的典範<ref>{{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/oxfordhistoryofm00town|title=The Oxford History of Modern War|last=Townshend|first=Charles|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=2000|pages=[https://archive.org/details/oxfordhistoryofm00town/page/14 14]—15|quote=Britain, however, with its strong tradition of minimal government — the 'night-watchman state' — vividly illustrated the speed of the shift [during World War I] from normalcy to drastic and all-embracing wartime powers like those contained in the Defence of the Realm Act.|isbn=0-19-285373-2}}</ref>。

== 詞源 ==
1862年，德國[[社會主義|社會主義者]][[斐迪南·拉萨尔|斐迪南·拉萨尔]]在柏林發表的一篇演講中首次用到了守夜人國家（{{lang-de|Nachtwächterstaat}}）一詞。他於當中批評了「[[資產階級|資產階級]][[自由主義|自由主義]][[小政府|小政府]]國家」的無所作為，就像守夜人一樣只是為了防止其他人盜取財產而存在。很快，此一用詞就被用於形容[[資本主義|資本主義]]政府。相關情況在自由主義開始用於代指更為參與社會事務的國家後也沒有改變<ref>Sawer, Marian (2003). ''The Ethical State?: Social Liberalism in Australia''. Melbourne University Publishing. [https://books.google.com/books?id=3TvKQ9TkiroC&pg=PA87&dq=night+watchman+state+Ferdinand+Lassalle&hl=en&sa=X&ei=vY5GT62NK-f10gHZgoygDg&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=night%20watchman%20state%20Ferdinand%20Lassalle&f=false p. 87] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3TvKQ9TkiroC&pg=PA87&dq=night+watchman+state+Ferdinand+Lassalle&hl=en&sa=X&ei=vY5GT62NK-f10gHZgoygDg&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=night%20watchman%20state%20Ferdinand%20Lassalle&f=false |date=20200804091002 }}. {{ISBN|0-522-85082-0}}. {{ISBN|978-0-522-85082-6}}.</ref>。

[[路德維希·馮·米塞斯|路德維希·馮·米塞斯]]於後來評論指，即使拉萨尔想令小政府看上去荒唐可笑，但沒什麼比起需要慮及「如何制作酸菜、裤扣及出版報紙」的政府更為可笑荒謬<ref>Von Mises, Ludwig (1927) [1922]. ''Liberalism''. [https://books.google.com/books?id=TMkSpFYc_SEC&pg=PA37&dq=night+watchman+state+Liberalism+mises&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Q5BGT5TiBunY0QH36sXwDQ&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q&f=false p. 37] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TMkSpFYc_SEC&pg=PA37&dq=night+watchman+state+Liberalism+mises&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Q5BGT5TiBunY0QH36sXwDQ&ved=0CDYQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20200804090425 }}.</ref>。

推廣它的人統稱為最小政府主義者（minarchists）。「minarchists」是「minimum」跟「-archy」的混成詞。[[始基|Arche]]（{{IPAc-en|ˈ|ɑr|k|i}}; {{lang-grc|[[:wikt:ἀρχή|ἀρχή]]}}）是希腊语用詞，意指「首位、权力」、「統治方法」、「帝王、王國」、「权威」、「命令」 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aalphabetic+letter%3D*a%3Aentry+group%3D318%3Aentry%3Da%29rxh%2F|title=Ἀρχή|script-title=el: Archy|trans-title=Archy|work=A Greek-English Lexicon|accessdate=2020-01-02|archive-date=2020-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927220300/http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aalphabetic+letter%3D*a%3Aentry+group%3D318%3Aentry%3Da%29rxh%2F|dead-url=no}}</ref>。最小政府主義者一詞為{{link-en|塞繆爾·愛德華·康金三世|Samuel Edward Konkin III}}於1980年所創<ref>Konkin III, Samuel Edward (1980). ''New Libertarian Manifesto''. p. 9.</ref>。

== 理念 ==
一般来说，最小政府主義者認為只有在邏輯上堅守[[互不侵犯原則|互不侵犯原則]]的國家，才能夠被證成<ref name="Gregory"/><ref name="Peikoff"/><ref name="Peikoff Part 1"/>。他們認為[[無政府資本主義|無政府資本主義]]是不切實際的，因為在這樣的一個社會執法者之間是容許競爭的，不足以使人遵守互不侵犯原則<ref>{{cite book|title=Anarchism/Minarchism: Is a Government Part of a Free Country?|publisher=Ashgate Publishing|year=2008|editor-last1=Long|editor-first1=Roderick T.|editor-last2=Machan|editor-first2=Tibor R.|isbn=978-0-7546-6066-8}}</ref>。另一個反對無政府資本主義的常見理由就是，私人辩护公司和法院公司往往会偏袒付钱给他们的人的利益<ref>{{cite journal|last=Holcombe|first=Randall G.|url=https://www.independent.org/pdf/tir/tir_08_3_1_holcombe.pdf|title=Government: Unnecessary but Inevitable|journal=The Independent Review|date=2004|accessdate=2020-01-02|archive-date=2019-08-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829143321/http://www.independent.org/pdf/tir/tir_08_3_1_holcombe.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

一些最小政府主義者認為國家會無可避免地繼續存在，故此任何嘗試建立無國家社會的努力都是徒勞無功的<ref>{{cite book|title=Frank H. Knight in Iowa City, 1919–1928|last=Emmett|first=Ross B.|date=12 August 2011|publisher=Emerald Group Publishing|isbn=978-1-78052-008-7}}</ref>。羅伯特·諾齊克在《無政府、國家與烏托邦》（1974）中推廣了守夜人國家此一概念，並認為它提供了一個基本框架，以讓尊重個人基本權利的政治制度能夠跟從，令國家的存在能夠被道德證成<ref name="Nozick 1974"/><ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2008|chapter=Minimal State|encyclopedia=The Encyclopedia of Libertarianism|publisher=SAGE Publications; Cato Institute|location=Thousand Oaks, California|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yxNgXs3TkJYC|last=Gordon|first=David|editor-last=Hamowy|editor-first=Ronald|pages=332–334|doi=10.4135/9781412965811.n204|isbn=978-1412965804|lccn=2008009151|oclc=750831024|title=存档副本|access-date=2020-05-23|archive-date=2020-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930100756/https://books.google.com/books?id=yxNgXs3TkJYC%2F|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

